article.description: Giddy Potts leads Middle Tennessee over Marshall 90-51
article.headline: Giddy Potts leads Middle Tennessee over Marshall 90-51
article.linkText: Giddy Potts leads Middle Tennessee over Marshall 90-51
article.story: MURFREESBORO, Tenn. -- Giddy Potts set career highs with eight 3-pointers and 28 points as Middle Tennessee turned an eight-point halftime lead into a 90-51 victory over Marshall on Thursday. Middle Tennessee (14-13, 7-7 Conference USA) led 34-26 at the break and let Marshall within 36-32 after three minutes of the second half. The Blue Raiders then scored 18 straight to start a 50-7 run over the next 14 minutes, leading 86-39 with three minutes left. The freshman Potts had all eight of his 3s during that stretch and finished 10 of 14 from the field. Marshall (9-17, 5-8) led 13-12 in the first half, but the Blue Raiders took the lead for good with a 10-0 run. Perrin Buford added 13 points and Darnell Harris scored 12 for Middle Tennessee, which snapped its own three-game skid while ending Marshall's three-game winning streak. JP Kambola scored 12 points for the Thundering Herd.
